ormance, data accuracy, and system scalability. [1]\n\nBeyond application development, I bring extensive DevOps expertise with Azure, AWS, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, and GitHub Actions. I have built CI/CD pipelines that reduce release cycles by 40\u202f% and implemented microservices and event\u2011driven architectures that enhance fault isolation and maintainability. My focus on security—implementing OAuth2/JWT, API hardening, and rigorous compliance workflows—has enabled clients like RiskCheck to achieve industry\u2011standard audit readiness. [1]\n\nI am drawn to [Company Name] because of your commitment to innovation and quality in [specific industry or technology focus]. I am confident that my blend of hands\u2011on development, system architecture, and cloud\u2011native operations would contribute immediately to your team’s success.\n\nThank you for considering my application. I look forward to the opportunity to discuss how my experience aligns with your needs. Please feel free to contact me at [phone] or [email] to schedule a conversation.\n\nSincerely,\n\n*Your Name*', 'reasoning_content': 'We need to respond to user query: "Based on Resume.pdf, am I a good candidate? If so, please create a cover letter." We have context of resume. We must use inline citations only when source has id attribute. In context, all sources have id="1" (same id). So we can cite [1]. The answer should evaluate whether they are a good candidate. They have extensive experience in backend, devops, security, enterprise clients. Likely yes.\n\nWe then need to create cover letter. It must be in the same language as user\'s query: English. Use citations where needed: use [1] to support claims. We might say: Yes, you are a strong candidate due to senior software developer/solution architect experience, etc. Cite [1].\n\nThen provide cover letter: header with name (not given) but we can use placeholder "Your Name". But the resume doesn\'t contain name; we can just say "Dear Hiring Manager," etc. Use content from resume: mention relevant skills: C#, PHP, WordPress, MySQL, Azure, AWS, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, etc. Mention projects: Ontario Sires Stakes, Park\'N Fly, RiskCheck, Caplans.\n\nProvide closing. Must not include XML tags.\n\nMake sure citations: e.g., "With over a decade of experience as a Senior Software Developer and Solution Architect at Whitecap Canada, delivering secure, scalable solutions for enterprise clients such as Miele Canada, Woodbine Entertainment Group, and others [1]."\n\nAlso mention devops and microservices.\n\nWe should answer: yes, you are a good candidate. Provide cover letter.\n\nNow produce final.'}}], 'object': 'chat.completion', 'usage': {'input_tokens': 772, 'output_tokens': 892, 'total_tokens': 1664, 'prompt_tokens': 772, 'completion_tokens': 892, 'response_token/s': 172.42, 'prompt_token/s': 6983.82, 'total_duration': 6259527797, 'load_duration': 334188455, 'prompt_eval_count': 772, 'prompt_eval_duration': 110541258, 'eval_count': 892, 'eval_duration': 5173295146, 'approximate_total': '0h0m6s', 'completion_tokens_details': {'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}}}
