  "coverletter": "Dear Hiring Manager,\n\nI am excited to apply for the Senior Software Developer / Solution Architect position at your organization. With over fifteen years of experience designing, building, and optimizing cloud\u2011native, enterprise\u2011grade applications, I bring a proven track record of delivering scalable, secure, and maintainable solutions for major Canadian clients.\n\nMy technical expertise spans the full stack: C#, .NET 6/7/8, ASP.NET Core/MVC, Entity Framework Core, as well as modern front\u2011end frameworks like React, Next.js, and Vue.js. I have architected and deployed applications on Azure and AWS, leveraging Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, and GitHub Actions to automate CI/CD pipelines and achieve high availability.\n\nNotable projects include modernizing legacy systems for the Ontario Sires Stakes/TIP racing program, implementing performance\u2011critical reservation systems for Park'N Fly, and enhancing compliance workflows for RiskCheck. These experiences required deep knowledge of secure data workflows, reporting automation, and multi\u2011location integration—skills directly relevant to the responsibilities outlined in your job description.\n\nBeyond technical delivery, I have mentored junior developers, led cross\u2011functional teams, and championed best practices such as clean architecture, automated testing, and DevSecOps. I am eager to bring this blend of technical leadership and hands\u2011on engineering to your team, driving innovation and excellence in your next-generation products.\n\nThank you for considering my application. I look forward to the opportunity to discuss how my background, skills, and passion align with your company’s goals.\n\nSincerely,\nAmir Nasser"
}
